Scott Sunderland (actor) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scott_Sunderland_(actor) 0 Scott Sunderland (19 September 1883 – 1956) was an English actor. Principally working on the stage, his few film roles included Colonel Pickering in the 1938 film adaptation of Shaw's Pygmalion and Sir John Colley in the 1939 film adaptation of Goodbye, Mr. Chips.
